OL,3,CBreakdown surge sparks Easter travel
OL,4,Cwarning for London motorists
OL,6,FTwo thirds of Londoners have broken
OL,7,Fdown on a motorway or major A-road in
OL,8,Ftheir lifetime, according to new data
OL,9,Ffrom the National Highways.
OL,11,FDrivers are being urged to carry out
OL,12,Fbasic safety checks, before travelling
OL,13,Fas spring breakdowns continue to rise.
OL,15,FLast year, there were 71,254
OL,16,Fbreakdowns recorded between March and
OL,17,FMay- a 25.6% rise from 2022.
OL,19,FColin Stevenson, Road Safety
OL,20,FInformation Lead for National Highways
OL,21,Fsaid:
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/5
